# TypeScript-First Node Layer

All user-facing Node.js code is authored in **TypeScript** with `strict: true`.

## Packages

| Package | Language | Output |
|---------|----------|--------|
| `packages/sdk` | TypeScript | `dist/cjs`, `dist/esm`, `.d.ts` |
| `packages/signaling` | TypeScript | `dist/cjs`, `dist/esm`, `.d.ts` |
| `examples/*` | TypeScript | compiled or `tsx` runner |
| `packages/bindings` | Rust + **JS loader only** | `index.js` (napi-rs prebuild loader) |

## Rules

- Source lives in `src/**/*.ts` — no hand-written `.js` in `src/`
- Bindings `index.d.ts` is generated by `napi build`, not hand-written
- Run `npm run format` before committing TS changes; CI runs `format:check` and `lint`
- After editing **`packages/sdk/src/**`**, run `npm run build --workspace=@node-webrtc-rust/sdk` so `dist/` types match source — see [`sdk-build.mdc`](sdk-build.mdc)
- Tests and examples use `.ts` (vitest)

## Formatting

Prettier is the source of truth for formatting. ESLint handles logic rules; `eslint-config-prettier` disables conflicting ESLint style rules.
